Ephemeris (1.0) by Terry R. McConnell

This is a basic commmand line program for calculating the ephemeris of a 
satellite of either the sun or the earth. Sets of orbital elements for 
significant objects are built-in, and others can be entered by means of
a dialogue. 

The command

make ephemeris

in this directory will build the program. Do ephemeris -h for usage 
information. 

ephemeris -d

while provide a list of built-in orbits

Orbits can be elliptical, parabolic, or hyperbolic. For example, the
command 

ephemeris -u 13 8/25/17 0:00

produces the output shown, a 1 month ephemeris of Oumuama (hyperbolic visitor
from instellar space) including its perihelion passage on September 9, 2017.

			Ephemeris (1.0)

