The command

ephemeris -V -u 13 -d

produces the following information on the orbit of Umuamua:

Elements of 1I/'Oumuamua (A/2017 U1) orbit epoch 0h UTC 11/22/2017
(Reference plane = ecliptic, origin = Sun)

t	Epoch (JD)		2458080.5
q	periapsis dist.		3.82838e+07 km	 0.255912 AU
e	Eccentricity		 1.201134
i	Inclination		122.742 deg
Omega	Longitude asc. node	24.5969 deg
w	Argument of perigee	241.811 deg
M	Mean anomaly		51.1576 deg (at the epoch)
n	mean motion		0.686747 deg/day


Other Orbital Parameters

b	Semi-minor axis		2.54731e+07 km	 0.170277 AU
p	Parameter		1.69491e+07 km	 0.113298 AU (Semi-latus rectum)
T	Periapsis Time		74.4927 days (nearest time) 
h	Energy			690.183 J/kg (ie. per kg of body)
|L|	Ang. Momentum		669211 km^2/sec (per kg)
v	True Anomaly		126.938 deg
wtilde	long. of periapsis	266.407 deg.
L	Mean long.		317.565 deg. (at epoch)
